ty Stouffer. Along with his brother, Mark, he also produced the TV series of John Denver specials for ABC in the late 1970s and early 1980s. Another half-dozen one-hour Specials for the National Geographic Society were also produced during that same time period. Stouffer's special \"The Predators\" was narrated by Robert Redford and his special \"The Man Who Loved Bears\" was narrated by Will Geer and Henry Fonda. Source: Wikidata; 01/08/2023", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2025-03-06T23:52:04.030443+11:00", "external_links": [{"id": 4638, "uri": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Marty_Stouffer"}], "uuid": "d1132640-1b05-4d12-b785-fc5b0604b18a", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "24689", "external_references": [{"id": 25515, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q6777562"}, {"id": 30174, "source": {"name": "VIAF", "slug": "viaf"}, "source_identifier": "40783195"}, {"id": 30175, "source": {"name": "LOC Auth", "slug": "loc-auth"}, "source_identifier": "n84156267"}, {"id": 30176, "source": {"name": "WorldCat", "slug": "worldcat"}, "source_identifier": "lccn-n84156267"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-06T23:52:04.030738+11:00"}, {"id": 74224, "name": "Mark Stouffer", "roles_in_work": [{"id": 2677719, "title": "At the crossroads: the story of America's endangered species", "work_id": 65024, "role": "co-producer", "role_id": 915, "is_primary": true}], "also_known_as": "", "date_of_birth": "", "date_of_death": "", "genders": [], "languages": [], "places_of_operation": [], "biography": "", "biography_author": null, "date_of_biography": "2023-05-09T12:33:00.805767+10:00", "external_links": [], "uuid": "85b9c016-221b-4261-9243-562dfdefee8e", "source": {"name": "Vernon", "slug": "vernon"}, "source_identifier": "24564", "external_references": [{"id": 35490, "source": {"name": "Wikidata", "slug": "wikidata"}, "source_identifier": "Q106282612"}], "date_modified": "2025-03-06T23:26:41.279276+11:00"},